{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"hasAccess": false, "showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "64b16aa0f23ac7d519f9b621", "type": "multipleCorrect", "level": 2, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 180, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76cfc52ffa3c944600e0"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba2"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "64b1672d25f94b8a85b91cd9", "title": "JEE Advanced 2023 (Paper 1)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "<p>A plane polarized blue light ray is incident on a prism such that there is no reflection from the surface of the prism. The angle of deviation of the emergent ray is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#948;</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>60</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi></msup></math> (see Figure-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>). The angle of minimum deviation for red light from the same prism is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>&#948;</mi><mi>min</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>30</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi></msup></math> (see Figure-<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>). The refractive index of the prism material for blue light is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>. Which of the following statement(s) is(are) correct?</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_advanced/1edbc0c9-ede6-452c-a192-27af9c924aa1.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 184px;\" /></p>", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "CMpme", "text": "The blue light is polarized in the plane of incidence", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "ccXgP", "text": "The angle of the prism is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>45</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi></msup></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "IO28J", "text": "The refractive index of the material of the prism for red light is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "zUIRc", "text": "The angle of refraction for blue light in air at the exit plane of the prism is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>60</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi></msup></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>For no reflection:</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_advanced/bb5d1bcb-6cb6-4aca-9adc-d5b0043c2ff9.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 242px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p><p>Applying Snell&#39;s law at left interface, we get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>sin</mi><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>sin</mi><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>30</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi></msup></math></p><p>Now, for given values</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#948;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>i</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>e</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>A</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>+</mo><mi>e</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>A</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>e</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi></math></p><p>Then,&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>30</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi></msup></math></p><p>For red light:</p><p>Expression to find minimum deviation is given by,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>&#948;</mi><mi>m</mi></msub></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></math></p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": {"videoId": "a9c112903b244cbfbb9269e266718b10", "provider": "vdocipher", "thumbnailLight": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/zzwbAj7toOy81.480.jpeg", "thumbnailDark": "https://d1z78r8i505acl.cloudfront.net/poster/zzwbAj7toOy81.480.jpeg", "premiumModules": [{"premiumModuleId": "6628114842d540dfcb148ecb", "isFree": false},